            "section": "Response to the letter of L. Santacroce regarding article \"Enhancing immunity in viral infections, with special emphasis on COVID-19: A review\" (Jayawardena et al.):"
        },
        {
            "text": "A COVID-19 patient with multiple complications reported a favourable outcome after administration of probiotics, including Lactobacillus acidophilus, Bifidobacterium and Saccharomyces boulardii, along with vitamins & minerals [6] . Similarly, a 9 years old boy diagnosed with COVID 19 exhibited disappearance of mild diarrhoea symptoms when administered probiotics [6] . The usefulness of probiotics in the treatment and prevention of viral infections are clear, due to their proven immunomodulatory activity and ability to stimulate interferon production [6] . Therefore the gut-lung axis explains the possible relationship likely to occur between respiratory diseases and the gut microbiome [2] . An ongoing clinical trial (NCT04366180) on supplementing probiotics (Lactobacillus Coryniformis K8) for the prevention of COVID-19 in healthcare workers will enable us to further understand their therapeutic benefits.",
